    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1" facs="EHRI-BF-19380509b_1.jpg"/>
            <p>Dear Sirs,</p>

            <p>I am here in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/6269131/england.html">England</placeName> as the authorised representative of the
                Board of Deputies of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> of <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">Burgenland</placeName> and the Orthodox <term type="subject"
                    ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735">Rabbis</term> of <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austria</placeName>. I have been here for 10 days already, but have
                unfortunately accomplished very little.</p>

            <p>In the name of many thousands of suffering people, I beg of you most urgently and desperately to support the case of the privately
                instituted <orgName ref="#ehri_bf_aid_committee_orthodox_vienna">Aid Committee of the Orthodox <term
                        ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewry</term> in <placeName
                        ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName></orgName> and especially the desperate need of the <term
                    ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> of <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">Burgenland</placeName>.</p>

            <p>[...]</p>
            <pb n="2" facs="EHRI-BF-19380509b_2.jpg"/>

            <p>In addition to this, we have to face the tragic problem of <hi rend="u">The</hi>
                <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">Burgenland</placeName>
                <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-101" type="subject">Refugees</term>, the full burden of which falls upon
                the <orgName ref="#ehri_bf_aid_committee_orthodox_vienna">Committee</orgName>.</p>

            <p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> of the <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">Burgenland</placeName>, mostly <term type="subject"
                    ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">families</term> settled there since centuries and distinguished by
                their conservative conduct, numbering about 3,000, were - as is sufficiently known - by means of tortures unheard of, compelled to
                charge themselves in a written statement with the commitment of different crimes. On the ground of these extorted protocols, their
                    <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-585">property was confiscated</term> and they
                themselves driven out of the country.</p>

            <p>One part of these <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> was deprived of all
                means, and driven to different frontiers - <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html"
                    >Czecho-Slovakia</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungary</placeName> and <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/7500737/federal-republic-of-yugoslavia.html">Jugo-Slavia</placeName>[!]. Among them, hunted in herds,
                the oldest victim was 83 years, the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824">youngest</term>
                3 weeks old. Among them were <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">families</term> who
                once possessed more than £100.000, and have to-day not a single penny left.</p>

            <p>In <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czecho-Slovakia</placeName> alone, there are more than fifty of
                these people driven out and now hidden in different <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819"
                    >families</term>, as they are there illegally without knowledge of the Authorities. Should the Authorities be informed of this
                state of affairs, they will be brought back to the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html"
                    >Austrian</placeName> frontier and the tragedy of <term type="subject"
                    ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-642">persecution</term> will start again.</p>

            <pb n="3" facs="EHRI-BF-19380509b_3.jpg"/>

            <p>Another part of these <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> are on the
                well-known <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3017382/republic-of-france.html">French</placeName> steamer in the <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/791630/danube-river.html">Danube</placeName> at <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/3045991/rajka.html">Rajka</placeName>. It is said that the <persName ref="#ehri_bf_basil_newton"
                    >English</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_bf_wilbur_j_carr">American</persName>
                <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1118">Consul</term> in <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName> have undertaken a guarantee for <term type="subject"
                    ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-203">emigration</term> on behalf of these <term
                    ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>.</p>

            <p>One part of these <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-629" type="subject">exiled</term> are still in the
                    <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">Burgenland</placeName>. Their businesses have been <term
                    type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-585">confiscated</term> ant they will have to go at short
                notice. The longest term, which has been fixed for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-629" type="subject"
                    >exile</term>, is the <date when="1938-05-25">25th of May</date>.</p>

            <p>The greatest part of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> of <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">Burgenland</placeName> is, however, in <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName> - having saved their bare existence [...].</p>

            <p>[...]</p>
            <pb n="4" facs="EHRI-BF-19380509b_4.jpg"/>

            <p>Yours sincerely,</p>

            <p><signatures><persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000425">Michal Weissmandl</persName>, <term
                        type="subect" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735">Rabbi</term>, <placeName
                        ref="http://www.geonames.org/3058531/nitra.html">Nitra, Č.S.R.</placeName></signatures></p>
